Bilevel programming
\[
\begin{aligned}
\min_{x, y} ~ & F(x, y) \\
\mathrm{s.t.} ~ & G(x, y) \geq 0 \\
& y \in \arg\min_y ~\{f(x, y): g(x, y) \geq 0\}
\end{aligned}
\]

Graphs are matrices


Adjacency matrix:
\[
A_{u, v} = \begin{cases}
1 & \text{if $v \in N(u)$} \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]

Incidence matrix: \[
B_{e, v} = \begin{cases}
1 & \text{if $e = \{u, v\}$} \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]
